==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Talebearer
<hw>Tale"bear`er</hw> <pr>(t⟦amac⟧l"b⟦acir⟧r`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>One who officiously tells tales; one who
impertinently or maliciously communicates intelligence, scandal, etc.,
and makes mischief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Spies and <qex>talebearers</qex>, encouraged by her father, did
their best to inflame her resentment.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Talebearing</ent>⟦br⟧
